cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR 

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with learning depth from monocular videos. The paper also addresses egomotion and object motion, which are related to robotics (cs.RO) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of differentiable warping and regularization techniques suggests a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the evaluation on datasets such as Cityscapes and KITTI, which are commonly used in computer vision research, and the mention of YouTube videos, which are a source of visual data, suggest a possible connection to graphics (cs.GR).
